headline: A look at Intel Capital before the 34-year-old firm strikes out on its own
summary: When Intel Capital announced its plans to spin out from semiconductor giant Intel in January, it came as a bit of a shock considering the firm has been operating as Intel's venture investment arm since 1991. In many ways this decision marks the end of an era for what's considered by some to be the first corporate venture capital firm of all time.
